# MANIFEST.custom -- Files preserved across automated refreshes
#
# Each entry: relative-path + brief reason.
# Refresh tools (e.g. create-repo) MUST read this file before any in-place
# update and skip listed paths (or merge via CUSTOM:start/CUSTOM:end
# sentinel comments where applicable).
#
# Path-with-sentinel-id form (e.g., README.md:CUSTOM:section_id) means:
# the file as a whole is generated, but the section marked with the named
# sentinel is preserved across refreshes.
#
# An empty MANIFEST.custom is fine if the repo currently has no custom
# content; the file's existence is the signal that the discipline applies.
#
# See __APF Library/CLAUDE.md "Universal archive convention" for the rule.

# Standard custom artifacts (every paper-companion repo)

APF_Reviewer_Walkthrough.ipynb     # hand-curated Colab notebook walkthrough
interactive_dag.html               # custom D3.js DAG with paper-specific node styling
docs/index.html                    # GitHub Pages landing with custom layout

# README.md and ai_context/*.md sections (sentinel-based partial preservation)
#
# These files are mostly template-generated by create-repo, but selected
# sections may carry hand-curated content marked with sentinel comments.
# Format inside the file:
#
#   <!-- CUSTOM:start id=section_id -->
#   ... custom content ...
#   <!-- CUSTOM:end id=section_id -->
#
# Refresh tools merge existing custom-marked sections into regenerated
# files at matching sentinels.  Sentinel ids must be unique within a file.
#
# Add an entry here in the form 'path:CUSTOM:section_id' to declare a
# section as preserved.  No entry needed if the file is fully regenerable.
